---
import PageLayout from '~/layouts/PageLayout.astro';
import Hero from '~/components/widgets/Hero.astro';

const metadata = {
  title: 'Terms & Conditions',
  description: 'Mom Helper USA service terms and conditions and privacy policy',
};
---

<PageLayout metadata={metadata}>
  <!-- Hero Widget -->
  <Hero
    tagline="Terms & Conditions"
    title="Service Terms and Conditions"
    subtitle="Terms applicable when using Mom Helper USA services"
  />

  <!-- Terms Content -->
  <section class="px-4 py-16 mx-auto max-w-4xl">
    <article class="prose prose-lg dark:prose-invert max-w-none">
      <p class="text-muted mb-8"><strong>Last Updated:</strong> January 1, 2025</p>

      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mt-12 mb-6">Article 1 (Purpose)</h2>
      <p class="mb-6">
        These terms and conditions are intended to define the basic matters regarding the rights, obligations,
        and responsibilities between Mom Helper USA (hereinafter referred to as "the Company") and users,
        as well as the service conditions and procedures for postpartum care and other home support services.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mt-12 mb-6">Article 2 (Definition of Terms)</h2>
      <ol class="list-decimal pl-6 mb-6 space-y-3">
        <li><strong>"Service"</strong> refers to postpartum care, babysitting, housekeeping, and caregiving services provided by the Company.</li>
        <li><strong>"User"</strong> refers to customers who use the services provided by the Company in accordance with these terms.</li>
        <li><strong>"Caregiver"</strong> refers to professional personnel dispatched by the Company to provide services.</li>
        <li><strong>"Commute Type"</strong> refers to a service format where the caregiver visits daily during set hours (9 AM - 5 PM).</li>
        <li><strong>"Live-in Type"</strong> refers to a service format where the caregiver stays at the user's home and provides 24-hour service.</li>
      </ol>

      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mt-12 mb-6">Article 3 (Effect and Amendment of Terms)</h2>
      <ol class="list-decimal pl-6 mb-6 space-y-3">
        <li>These terms shall be effective for all users who wish to use the service.</li>
        <li>The Company may amend these terms as necessary within the scope of applicable laws, and amended terms shall become effective upon posting on the website.</li>
        <li>If users do not agree to the amended terms, they may discontinue service use and terminate the contract.</li>
      </ol>

      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mt-12 mb-6">Article 4 (Provision and Changes of Services)</h2>
      <ol class="list-decimal pl-6 mb-6 space-y-3">
        <li>The Company provides the following services:
          <ul class="list-disc pl-6 mt-3 space-y-2">
            <li>Postpartum care services (mother care, newborn care, household support)</li>
            <li>Babysitter and nanny services</li>
            <li>Housekeeping services</li>
            <li>Caregiving services</li>
          </ul>
        </li>
        <li>Service content is determined according to individual contracts with users.</li>
        <li>The Company may change the service content for reasonable reasons and will notify users immediately.</li>
      </ol>

      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mt-12 mb-6">Article 5 (Establishment of Service Contract)</h2>
      <ol class="list-decimal pl-6 mb-6 space-y-3">
        <li>Service contracts are established upon user application and Company acceptance.</li>
        <li>The Company may refuse service provision in the following cases:
          <ul class="list-disc pl-6 mt-3 space-y-2">
            <li>When the application contains false information, omissions, or errors</li>
            <li>When service provision is technically impossible</li>
            <li>Other cases deemed necessary by the Company</li>
          </ul>
        </li>
      </ol>

      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mt-12 mb-6">Article 6 (Reservation and Deposit)</h2>
      <ol class="list-decimal pl-6 mb-6 space-y-3">
        <li>Service reservations should be made at least 1-2 months before the expected due date.</li>
        <li>A deposit must be paid according to the service period for reservation confirmation.</li>
        <li>The deposit is included in the total service fee and will be settled after service completion.</li>
        <li>50% of the deposit will be refunded for cancellations made at least 7 days before service start.</li>
        <li>No refund for cancellations made within 7 days of service start.</li>
      </ol>

      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mt-12 mb-6">Article 7 (Fees and Payment)</h2>
      <ol class="list-decimal pl-6 mb-6 space-y-3">
        <li>Service fees vary according to service type, period, and region, and are specified at contract signing.</li>
        <li>Payment methods include check, Zelle, cash, and wire transfer.</li>
        <li>Deposit is due upon reservation confirmation, and balance is due before or during service period.</li>
        <li>Additional pay for holiday work will be notified in advance.</li>
      </ol>

      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mt-12 mb-6">Article 8 (Service Schedule Changes and Cancellation)</h2>
      <ol class="list-decimal pl-6 mb-6 space-y-3">
        <li>Free schedule changes are available up to 7 days before service start.</li>
        <li>Changes within 7 days of service start may incur change fees.</li>
        <li>The Company is not responsible for service unavailability due to force majeure such as natural disasters or epidemics.</li>
      </ol>

      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mt-12 mb-6">Article 9 (Company's Obligations)</h2>
      <ol class="list-decimal pl-6 mb-6 space-y-3">
        <li>The Company dispatches professional and experienced caregivers to provide quality service.</li>
        <li>The Company conducts background checks on caregivers and provides necessary training.</li>
        <li>The Company protects users' personal information and complies with relevant laws.</li>
        <li>The Company responds promptly to issues arising during service provision.</li>
      </ol>

      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mt-12 mb-6">Article 10 (User's Obligations)</h2>
      <ol class="list-decimal pl-6 mb-6 space-y-3">
        <li>Users must comply with these terms and relevant laws.</li>
        <li>Users must cooperate to ensure caregivers can work in a safe and comfortable environment.</li>
        <li>Users must disclose all relevant information in advance, including pets and special health conditions.</li>
        <li>Users may not request tasks outside the scope of service from caregivers.</li>
        <li>Users must respect and treat caregivers courteously.</li>
      </ol>

      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mt-12 mb-6">Article 11 (Service Scope and Limitations)</h2>
      <ol class="list-decimal pl-6 mb-6 space-y-3">
        <li>Caregivers are not medical professionals and do not provide medical services (injections, medication administration, etc.).</li>
        <li>In emergencies, caregivers will immediately contact 911 and notify users.</li>
        <li>Caregivers provide services only within the scope specified in the contract.</li>
      </ol>

      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mt-12 mb-6">Article 12 (Liability and Indemnification)</h2>
      <ol class="list-decimal pl-6 mb-6 space-y-3">
        <li>The Company is responsible for damages caused to users by the caregiver's intentional or gross negligence.</li>
        <li>However, the Company is not responsible in the following cases:
          <ul class="list-disc pl-6 mt-3 space-y-2">
            <li>Force majeure such as natural disasters, war, or riots</li>
            <li>Cases attributable to user fault</li>
            <li>Unforeseeable accidents during normal service performance</li>
          </ul>
        </li>
        <li>Property damage will be resolved through consultation depending on circumstances.</li>
      </ol>

      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mt-12 mb-6">Article 13 (Personal Information Protection)</h2>
      <ol class="list-decimal pl-6 mb-6 space-y-3">
        <li>The Company protects users' personal information in accordance with relevant laws.</li>
        <li>Collected personal information is used only for service provision purposes and is not provided to third parties.</li>
        <li>Users may request to view, modify, or delete their personal information at any time.</li>
      </ol>

      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mt-12 mb-6">Article 14 (Dispute Resolution)</h2>
      <ol class="list-decimal pl-6 mb-6 space-y-3">
        <li>In case of disputes related to service use, the Company and users shall make efforts to resolve them amicably through mutual consultation.</li>
        <li>If consultation fails, the matter shall be resolved in the competent court according to California state law.</li>
      </ol>

      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mt-12 mb-6">Article 15 (Governing Law and Jurisdiction)</h2>
      <ol class="list-decimal pl-6 mb-6 space-y-3">
        <li>These terms shall be interpreted and applied according to the laws of the State of California, USA.</li>
        <li>Lawsuits related to service use shall be filed in the court having jurisdiction over the Company's headquarters location.</li>
      </ol>

      <div class="bg-blue-50 dark:bg-slate-800 p-8 rounded-lg mt-12">
        <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-4">Contact Us</h3>
        <p class="mb-4">If you have any questions about these terms, please contact us:</p>
        <p class="mb-2"><strong>Mom Helper USA</strong></p>
        <p class="mb-2"><strong>Phone:</strong> (213) 808-4415</p>
        <p class="mb-2"><strong>Email:</strong> momhelperusa10@gmail.com</p>
        <p><strong>Kakao Talk:</strong> momhelper.usa</p>
      </div>

      <p class="text-center text-muted mt-12 pt-8 border-t">
        These terms are effective as of January 1, 2025.
      </p>
    </article>
  </section>
</PageLayout>
